The paper discusses adapting a software model checker for runtime verification, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The modifications made to the model checker are small and self-contained, indicating a focus on programming languages (cs.PL) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also mentions the software under test communicating with the wider environment, which could involve security concerns (cs.CR) and distributed computing (cs.DC).
